Techxonia Inc. Privacy Policy 
for
In-Case of Emergency (ICE) application


Last Updated: August 23, 2017 06:10 PM GMT+5:45 


What Does This Privacy Policy Cover? 
In your dealings with ICE you may provide us with Device Permission for personal access i.e SMS Permission.
SMS Permission for the purposes of this Privacy Policy means used for accessing features related to the User's 
messaging including the sending, receiving and reading of SMS. This Privacy Policy does not apply to the practices of 
entities that we do not own or control, or to individuals that we do not employ or manage. 
More generally, we think of our privacy policy as a feature and hope that youâ€™ll agree.  


Android Permissions
We request the following android permissions for the following reasons:
android.permission.WAKE_LOCK. Needed to prevent the app from sleep
android.permission.RECEIVE_BOOT_COMPLETED. Needed to notify the app after reboot
android.permission.SEND_SMS. Needed to send SMS
android.permission.READ_CONTACT. Needed to retrieve name and phone


Enforcement 
If you have any questions about this Privacy Policy, you should first contact us at techxonia@gmail.com

Contacting Us 
Any questions about this Privacy Policy should be addressed to techxonia@gmail.com
